The _new_ way to declare references is to have a "reference" attribute. It is no longer supported to implicitly declare a reference by the "name" attribute... however we allow this for backward compatibility and will eventually get rid of the logic to allow it.

The altered code was only looking to see if the identity was a reference by looking at the "name" attribute, however in most cases now, this will not work and thus the filter is failing to remove identities that should not be removed.
